snippet.textDisplay: Bless him. Apart from being famous I relate to alot of what was said in this interview. From addiction to anxiety and depression being unwell/ tired trying your hardest to be healthy but feeling like absolute shit every day and wondering why. Good for you for speaking your truth and sharing that with the world it's a very brave thing to do. One thing you said about people saying bad things about you on social media. Just thought I'd share something that helped me in my early recovery (I'm 7 years sober by the way) when someone talks bad about you just remember that they are suffering and sick, I like to ask myself what have they been through to make them like that? And it takes me from a place of resentment to a place of compassion. Because ultimately that resentment just lives inside of us. It's not just you that thinks we have bad in us either I totally get what you said and it is about making the choice every day to do the right thing. But I do feel that over time if we keep making the right choices the temptation will become less and less. Thanks again for sharing I wish you all the best

snippet.textDisplay: One more thing...Zane gives amazing interviews. He doesn't interrupt, gives the person time and space to respond and he's very supportive of his interviewee. With that being said, when Justin stepped on the scene, I was already an adult. I looked at him as another young, fresh teen doing pop music. Cute for the tweens, but I didn't pay him a whole lot of attention. Seeing him tell his story and all that he has been through has been refreshing and has made me particularly protective in an unexpected way. I guess because I can relate. We all have our form of dysfunction, and for people to cast judgment upon him without really knowing him is baseless and cruel. I have read some malicious comments time and time again about Hailey, and I'm convinced people are nasty only because they can't be her and they're envious. Life is hard enough for all of us without the hostility of who he should have married, which is his damn business anyway. I wish them nothing but the best God has to offer. Which is always the best and nothing less.
